    "trade_plan_fix": "An R:R bug was found and fixed during this milestone: target1 previously used the nearest S/R level (often very close), while the stop used a much wider 1x ATR -- 100% of planned trades had R:R < 1.0 (median 0.21) before the fix. build_trade_plan now floors the target at k_target/k_stop (2.0) and only extends it when real S/R sits genuinely further out.",
    "honest_state": "Post-fix, directional accuracy sits near 50% and expectancy is still negative for both instruments -- the raw rule-based swing engine (without PCR/OI) shows no validated edge yet on 2yr of history. This is the expected state of a first-pass model before weight optimization (M6) and before the live PCR/OI/basis factors (which ARE working, see M1/M3) are exercised forward by the paper-trading ledger."
